**Abstract:**
Major essay titled "On Archbishop Romero and Some Aspects of Autonomy" examining Oscar Romero's martyrdom through the lens of Sartrean autonomy. Uses the film "Romero" as reference point. Argues against Sartre's abstract conception of autonomy, proposing that genuine autonomy requires deep commitment. Explores Christian autonomy as fidelity to the gospel and critiques Sartre's failure to account for the weight of circumstances on human freedom.

**AI Recommendation:** Published or near-publication quality essay; major work on Romero and autonomy.

